<p><abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ recipient's copy ]">RC</abbr> (<span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ American Philosophical Society, Philadelphia, Pennsylvania ]">PPAP</span>). At head of text, in Franklins hand, is the following: Extract of Letter from<span class="space" title="space in original source" style="padding-left:1.5em; padding-right:1.5em;"></span>to<span class="space" title="space in original source" style="padding-left:1.5em; padding-right:1.5em;"></span>dated<span class="space" title="space in original source" style="padding-left:1.5em; padding-right:1.5em;"></span>&amp;c.; along the margin from the beginning of the letter down to the complimentary close, there is a line that Franklin must have drawn to indicate what parts were to be copied in the extract, which may have been intended for Chevalli.</p></div>
